        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Vladimir Saveliev",
          "email": "vladimir.saveliev@oracle.com",
          "date": "2012-09-09 08:57:03.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-1901 ldiskfs: compile error for sles11 when JBD2_DEBUG is on",
        "message": "LU-1901 ldiskfs: compile error for sles11 when JBD2_DEBUG is on\n\nThe only change is the below hunk for ext4/inode.c:ext4_forget():\n        jbd_debug(4, \"forgetting bh %p: is_metadata = %d, mode %o, \"\n-                 \"data mode %xn\",\n+                 \"data mode %Lxn\",\n                  bh, is_metadata, inode->i_mode,\n                  test_opt(inode->i_sb, DATA_FLAGS));\n\nIt is needed because for sles11 s_mount_opt of struct ext4_sb_info\nis changed to unsigned long long.\n\nSigned-off-by: Vladimir Saveliev <vladimir.saveliev@oracle.com>\nChange-Id: I59646b821b83eed08a67124a9f52ab8dcb9b46ae\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
